==English==

===Pronunciation===
[[SAMPA]]: [h@"waI@n]

===Alternative spellings===
'''[[Hawai'ian]]'''

===Proper noun===
'''Hawaiian'''

# A [[descendant]] of the peoples [[inhabiting]] the [[Hawaiian islands]] prior to [[European]] contact.
# The [[Wiktionary:Hawaiian index|Hawaiian language]].
# A [[resident]] of the U.S. state of [[Hawaii]].*

====Translations====
*Chinese:[[夏威夷人]](1),[[夏威夷语]](2)
*Finnish: [[havaijilainen]] (1,3), [[havaiji]] (2)
*German: [[Hawaiianer]] ''m'' (1,3); [[Hawaiianerin]] ''f'' (1, 3); [[Hawaiianisch]] ''n'' (2)

===Adjective===
'''Hawaiian'''  (''no'' {{compar}} ''or'' {{superl}})

# [[Descended]] from the peoples [[inhabiting]] the [[Hawaiian islands]] prior to [[European]] contact.
# Of or having to do with the Hawaiian race, culture, or language.
# Of or having to do with the culture of the U.S. state of Hawaii.
# Of or having to do with a resident of the U.S. state of Hawaii.*

[*] These senses are generally deprecated by Hawaii residents, who tend to prefer reserving the word for referring specifically to the Native Hawaiian race.

